r/TrueOffMyChest

u/Street-Level-7850

1d

Our newborn (1mo) is making me see my wife as "stupid," and it's turning me into an asshole. I feel awful and need to stop.

Guys, I'm in a really bad place and I need a reality check.

My wife is my best friend. I love her, she's a great person, kind, loyal, all of it. We've been married 3 years.

But I feel like my wife is... slow. I know that sounds horrible, and I feel like a total asshole even typing it. For years, it's been a thing. She needs me for anything technical or requires problem-solving. Like, I've had to FaceTime her to show her how to find something in her banking app multiple times. It's not just tech stuff either, it's a bunch of things. We have a totally different sense of humor. I had to literally explain to her what a "meme" was a while back.
